Installed snap version on Ubuntu 18.04 LTS - don't forget to give permission to access all drives on your system. 

(Sorta silly by snap package designers to not set that as a default, when the purpose of the program is to display your filesystem) 

qFSview mapped my large drives fast and the graphics display is very clear and informative at the top level. Don't have to dig down into the tree leaves until you see the info you need.
